        <div class="place">
        <h2><strong>Jaipur</strong></h2>
            <img src="jaipur.jpg" alt="Jaipur">
            <p>Jaipur, the Pink City, combines Rajputana heritage with vibrant markets. Don't miss the iconic Hawa Mahal and indulge in a shopper's paradise with traditional textiles, jewelry, and crafts. December is an ideal time to explore its rich history and cultural beauty.</p>
            <ul class="list">
<li><strong>Best Time to Visit Jaipur:</strong> October to March.</li>
<li><strong>Tourist Attractions in Jaipur:</strong> City Palace, Hawa Mahal, Amber Fort and Palace, Nahargarh Fort, Jaygarh Fort, Jantar Mantar Observatory, Birla Mandir.</li>
<li><strong>Things to Do in Jaipur:</strong> Wildlife safari, Shopping Souvenirs, Textiles, and Gems, Exploring the Forts and Palaces</li></ul>
        </div>

        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Jaisalmer</strong></h2>
            <img src="jaisalmer.jpg" alt="Jaisalmer">
           <p>Jaisalmer, the Golden City in Rajasthan, captivates with its yellow sandstone fortress—Jaisalmer Fort—and intricate palaces. Explore narrow lanes and ancient temples within. Indulge in vibrant markets and savor local delights like Dal Bati Churma. The mesmerizing Sam Sand Dunes beckon with camel rides and desert safaris, making Jaisalmer a unique Rajasthan gem.</p>
<ul class="list">
<li><strong>Best Time to Visit Jaisalmer:</strong> September to April.</li>
<li><strong>Tourist Attractions in Jaisalmer:</strong> Jaisalmer Fort, Sam dunes, Gadisagar Lake, Tanot Mata Temple.</li>
<li><strong>Things to Do in Jaisalmer:</strong>  Attend the Desert festival of Jaisalmer in January – February, take a camel safari to the Sam dunes, visit the Longewala border.</li></ul>
        </div>



        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Jodhpur</strong></h2>
            <img src="jodhpur.jpg" alt="Mysore">
            <p>Jodhpur, the Blue City of Rajasthan, enchants with its iconic Mehrangarh Fort offering panoramic views. Explore the exquisite Jaswant Thada and embrace the city's warmth as the Sun City. Winter is the ideal time, with vibrant festivals in September adding to its charm. Jodhpur is a must-visit for its historic forts, palaces, and cultural richness.</p>
            <ul class="list">
<li><strong>Best Time to Visit Jodhpur:</strong> November to February.</li>
<li><strong>Tourist Attractions in Jodhpur:</strong>Mehrangarh Fort, the Umaid Bhawan Palace, the Mandore Gardens, the Jaswant Thada, the Kalyana Lake, and Garden, the Ghanta Ghar, Sardar Samand Lake, and Masuria Hills.</li>
<li><strong>Things to Do in Jodhpur:</strong>Visit the palaces, and forts, and taste the local delicacies.</li></ul>
        </div>

        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Udaipur</strong></h2>
            <img src="udaipur.jpg" alt="Udaipur">
            <p >Udaipur, the City of Lakes, beckons with its stunning palaces and serene ambiance. Explore the opulence of City Palace, and be captivated by the beauty of Lake Pichola. This Rajasthan gem is renowned for vibrant handicrafts and offers a memorable dining experience with traditional Rajasthani thalis at rooftop restaurants.</p>
            <ul class="list">
<li><strong>Best Time to Visit Udaipur:</strong> July to September and November to February.</li>
<li><strong>Tourist Attractions in Udaipur:</strong>Lake Pichola, Fateh Sagar Lake, City Palace, Jag Mandir, Udai Sagar Lake, Jagdish Temple, Monsoon Palace, Swaroop Sagar, Kumbhalgarh Fort.</li>
<li><strong>Things to Do in Udaipur:</strong>Boating at Lake Pichola, visiting the palaces, visiting Kumbhalgarh fort, photography.</li></ul>
        </div>

        <div class="place">
            <h2><strong>Chittorgarh</strong></h2>
            <img src="chittorgarh.jpg" alt="Chittorgarh">
            <p>Chittorgarh is a historic city, famous for its magnificent forts, palaces, and temples. The city's top attraction is the Chittorgarh Fort, a massive fortress that is perched atop a hill and offers stunning views of the surrounding countryside. The Vijay Stambh, a towering victory tower that is adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures, is amidst the captivating tourist attractions in Chittorgarh. Visitors can climb to the top of the tower to witness the stunning views of the city.</p>
             <ul class="list">
<li><strong>Best Time to Visit Chittorgarh:</strong>October to March.</li>
<li><strong>Tourist Attractions in Chittorgarh:</strong>Chittorgarh Fort, Rana Kumbha’s Palace, Fateh Prakash Palace, Rani Padmini’s Palace, Kumbhaswamini Temple, Kirti Stambh, Vijay Stambha, Kalika Mata temple.</li>
<li><strong>Things to Do in Chittorgarh:</strong>Listening to the folk tales, Savoring authentic Rajasthani cuisine.</li></ul>
        </div>
        
